{"title_page": "Mark Lee (singer)", "text_new": "{{unreliable sources|date=June 2019}}\n{{short description|Canadian-Korean rapper}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Watermelon Boi\n| birth_name         = Mark Spiderman Lee \n| native_name        = \uc774\ub9c8\ud06c\n| image              = 181012 Mark KBS '\ubba4\uc9c1\ubc45\ud06c' \ub9ac\ud5c8\uc124 \ucd9c\uadfc\uae38 \uc9c1\ucea0 \uc601\uc0c1.png\n| caption            = Mark Lee in October 2018\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1999|8|2}}\n| birth_place        = [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| nationality        = Canadian\n| other_names        = Lee Min-hyung\n| education          = [[School of Performing Arts Seoul]]\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Rapper|singer|songwriter}}\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background       = solo_singer\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[hip-hop]]}}\n| instrument       = {{hlist|Vocals}}\n| years_active     = 2013\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[SM Entertainment|SM]]|[[Avex Trax]]|[[Capitol Records|Capitol]]}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[NCT (band)|NCT]]|[[NCT 127]]|[[NCT U]]|[[NCT Dream]]|[[SuperM]]|[[SM Rookies]]|[[SM Town]]}}\n}}\n| module2            = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes\n| title           = [[Korean name]]\n| hangul          = \uc774\ubbfc\ud615\n| hanja           = {{linktext|\u674e|\u654f|\u4ea8}}\n| rr              = I Minhyeong\n| mr              = Yi Minhy\u014fng\n| hangulstage     = \ub9c8\ud06c\n| rrstage         = Ma Keu\n| mrstage         = Ma K'\u016d\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Mark Lee''' (born August 2, 1999), known professionally as '''Mark''', is a Canadian rapper and singer-songwriter based in South Korea. He is best known as a member of the South Korean boy group [[NCT (band)|NCT]] and its sub-units NCT U, [[NCT 127]], and [[NCT Dream]]. Mark made his debut in April 2016 as a member of rotational unit NCT U, became a member of Seoul-based fixed unit NCT 127 in July 2016 and also a member of NCT Dream in August 2016. In October 2019, Mark debuted as a member of the supergroup [[SuperM]].\n\n==Career==\n===2013\u20132015: SM Rookies===\nIn 2012, Mark joined [[SM Entertainment]] after passing the SM Global Audition in Canada in 2010.\n\nIn December 2013, Mark was introduced as a member of [[SM Rookies]], a pre-debut training team managed by SM Entertainment.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mydaily.co.kr/new_yk/html/read.php?newsid=201312171039311138|title='SM\ub8e8\ud0a4\uc988' \ub9c8\ud06c\u00b7\uc9c0\uc131\u00b7\ud55c\uc194 \uc804\uaca9\uacf5\uac1c, \uc548\ubb34\uac00 \ud1a0\ub2c8\ud14c\uc2a4\ud0c0 \uadf9\ucc2c|last=Jeon|first=Won|date=December 13, 2013|publisher=MyDaily|accessdate=July 18, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Mark appeared on [[Exo 90:2014]], a reality TV Show starring [[Exo (band)|Exo]], alongside other members of the SM Rookies program, where they performed songs and recreated music videos of prominent 90s [[K-pop]] idols.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.osen.co.kr/article/G1109972619|title=[\uc5b4\uc800\uaed8TV] \u2018\uc5d1\uc18c902014\u2019 K\ud31d \uc2dc\ud5d8, 90 \ubc18\uac11\uace0 2014 \uc0c8\ub86d\uace0|last=Kim|first=Sara|date=October 4, 2014|publisher=Osen|accessdate=July 18, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Mark appeared on [[Disney Channel Korea]]'s ''[[The Mickey Mouse Club]]'' as a Mouseketeer alongside other members of the SM Rookies program, some of which are currently in [[NCT Dream]]. The show aired from July 23 to December 17, 2015 and was hosted by [[Leeteuk]] of [[Super Junior]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tvreport.co.kr/?c=news&m=newsview&idx=743716|title=\ub514\uc988\ub2c8\ucc44\ub110, \ud55c\uad6d\ud310 \u2018\ubbf8\ud0a4\ub9c8\uc6b0\uc2a4\ud074\ub7fd\u2019 \uc81c\uc791 \u2018SM \ub8e8\ud0a4\uc988 \ucd9c\uc5f0\u2019|last=Hwang|first=Geung-ji|date=July 9, 2015|publisher=TV Report|accessdate=July 18, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n===2016\u2013present: NCT and solo endeavors===\nIn April 2016, SM Entertainment confirmed Mark alongside five other members of the SM Rookies program to debut as members of [[NCT (band)|NCT]] and its first subgroup, NCT U. On April 9, Mark, alongside [[Lee Tae-yong|Taeyong]], Doyoung, [[Ten (singer)|Ten]] and Jaehyun debuted with the digital single \"The 7th Sense\", which he and Taeyong participated in the writing of.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201604061758581112853_2|title=NCT U confirms lineup, set to unveil singles 'The 7th Sense,' 'Without You'|last=Son|first=Ji-hyoung|date=April 6, 2016|publisher=[[The Korea Herald]]|accessdate=April 28, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2016, SM confirmed Mark as a member of NCT's second subgroup, [[NCT 127]], alongside Taeyong, Taeil, Yuta, Jaehyun, Winwin and Haechan. NCT 127 made their official debut with ''[[NCT 127 (EP)|NCT #127]]'' and title track \"Fire Truck\" on July 10, 2016.<ref name=genre>{{cite web|url=http://pop.heraldcorp.com/view.php?ud=201607101242101223011_1|title=NCT 127 \uc804\uace1 \uc74c\uc6d0 \uacf5\uac1c, \ubcf4\ub108\uc2a4\ud2b8\ub799\uae4c\uc9c0 \ucd1d 7\uace1 \uc218\ub85d|date=July 10, 2016|website=Herald Corporation|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2016, SM confirmed Mark as a member of NCT's third subgroup, [[NCT Dream]], alongside Renjun, Jeno, Haechan, Jaemin, Chenle and Jisung. The group made their official debut on August 24, 2016, with the single \"Chewing Gum\".\n\nIn September 2016, Mark featured on [[Henry Lau]]'s \"Going Through Your Heart\", an original soundtrack for the [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]] drama, [[Sweet Stranger and Me]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/909461wpp/henry-ncts-mark-plus-kim-jong-kook-sing-ost-man-living-house|title= Henry And NCT\u2019s Mark Plus Kim Jong Kook To Sing OST For \"The Man Living In Our House\"|date=October 24, 2016|website=Soompi|language=en}}</ref> This marked his first solo endeavour since debuting under NCT. \n \nIn January 2017, Mark joined ''[[High School Rapper]]'', a survival hip hop reality TV show which aired on [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]].<ref name=\"crap-source1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/935159wpp/ncts-mark-audition-mnets-new-hip-hop-show-high-school-rapper|title= NCT\u2019s Mark To Audition For Mnet\u2019s New Hip Hop Show \"High School Rapper\"|date=January 9, 2017|website=Soompi|language=en}}</ref> He made it to the finals and performed an original song, \"Drop\" featuring labelmate, [[Kang Seul-gi|Seulgi]] of [[Red Velvet (group)|Red Velvet]]. He subsequently placed 7th overall.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/967909wpp/watch-high-school-rapper-reveals-final-winner-performances-special-guests|title= Watch: \"High School Rapper\" Reveals Final Winner And Performances With Special Guests|date=April 1, 2017|website=Soompi|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2017, Mark collaborated with Exo's [[Xiumin]] on single, [[Young & Free]]. The single was released through [[SM Station Season 2|Season 2]] of SM Entertainment's digital music project [[SM Station]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/music/now/read?oid=311&aid=0000749346|title=\uc5d1\uc18c \uc2dc\uc6b0\ubbfc\u00b7NCT \ub9c8\ud06c, 'SM\uc2a4\ud14c\uc774\uc158'\uc73c\ub85c \uc2a4\ud398\uc15c \ub4c0\uc624 \uacb0\uc131|access-date=2017-06-29|language=ko}}</ref> In the same month, Mark appeared in the first season of the music variety show ''Snowball Project''. He teamed up with [[Park Jae-jung (singer)|Park Jae-jung]] and released \"Lemonade Love\" on July 21, also through SM Station, which was produced by former labelmate Henry Lau and [[Yoon Jong-shin]].<ref name=\"snowballproject\">{{cite web |title=\"\ub208\ub369\uc774 \ucd9c\uaca9\"...\ubc15\uc7ac\uc815X\ub9c8\ud06c, \u2018\ub808\ubaa8\ub124\uc774\ub4dc \ub7ec\ube0c\u2019 \uc624\ub298(21\uc77c) \ubc1c\ud45c |url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/014/0003847621 |website=n.news.naver.com |accessdate=June 30, 2019 |language=ko |date=July 21, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/2017/05/23/sm-mystic-entertainment-team-new-music-variety-show/|title=Parc Jae Jung And NCT's Mark Are The First Team-Up For SM And Mystic Entertainment's New Variety Show {{!}} Soompi|website=www.soompi.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-07}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2018, Mark was named as one of the main emcees of the music program ''[[Show! Music Core]]''. He subsequently left the program in January 2019 to focus on activities with NCT 127.<ref name=\"showmucic\">{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=213&aid=0001014733|title=\uc639\uc131\uc6b0\u00b7\ubbf8\ub098\u00b7\ub9c8\ud06c, '\uc74c\uc545\uc911\uc2ec' \u65b0 MC \ubc1c\ud0c1 [\uacf5\uc2dd]|date=January 26, 2018|website=Herald Corporation|language=ko}}</ref>\nIn May 2018, he became a regular cast member on the [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] reality TV show ''[[It's Dangerous Beyond The Blankets]]''.<ref name=\"blankets\">{{cite news|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201805031602080410|title=MBC \uce21 \"NCT \ub9c8\ud06c \u2018\uc774\ubd88\ubc16\uc740 \uc704\ud5d8\ud574\u2019 \ucd9c\uc5f0 \ub17c\uc758\uc911\"|date=May 3, 2018}}</ref> In October 2018, Mark released the song \"Dream Me\" with Red Velvet's [[Joy (singer)|Joy]] for the soundtrack of the KBS drama ''[[The Ghost Detective]].''\n\nOn December 31, 2018, Mark became the first member to officially graduate from NCT Dream.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=109&aid=0003850884|title=\"[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5] NCT \ub9c8\ud06c, \uc62c\ud574 \ub9c8\uc9c0\ub9c9\uc73c\ub85c NCT DREAM \uc878\uc5c5\u2026\uc878\uc5c5\uc1a1 \uc218\ub85d\"|date=August 26, 2018|accessdate=July 1, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nOn August 7, 2019, Mark was confirmed as a member of [[SuperM]], a \"K-pop supergroup\" created by SM Entertainment in collaboration with [[Capitol Records]]. The group's promotions began in October and were  focused at the American market.<ref>{{cite news |author1=Jeff Benjamin |title=Super M, 'The Avengers Of K-Pop,' Unveiled By SM Entertainment And Capitol Music Group |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jeffbenjamin/2019/08/07/super-m-the-avengers-of-k-pop-unveiled-by-sm-entertainment-and-capitol-music-group/#355dfa061381 |accessdate=14 August 2019 |publisher=Forbes |date=7 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=SM Entertainment and Capitol Records Team Up to Launch Super M |url=https://www.billboard.com/video/bbnews080819tiffanykpop2-8526949 |accessdate=14 August 2019 |publisher=Billboard |date=8 August 2019}}</ref> SuperM's [[SuperM (EP)|self-titled debut EP]] was released on October 4, 2019 with lead single \"Jopping\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8532879/superm-the-1st-mini-album-billboard-200-no-1|title=SuperM Debuts at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Albums Chart With 'The 1st Mini Album'|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-10-28}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2020, it was announced by SM Entertainment that Mark would return to and take part in NCT Dream future activities, as the sub-unit was to be re-branded and shifted away from its previous age-based graduation system.<ref>https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9357513/nct-dream-new-album-reload-return-of-mark</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|NCT discography|SuperM#Discography}}\n\n===Songs===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\" | Title\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! colspan=\"2\" | Peak chart<br />positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Sales\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Album\n|-\n!  style=\"width:4em;font-size:90%\" |[[Gaon Music Chart|KOR<br />Gaon]]<br /><ref name=\"Gaon\">{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/|title=Gaon Chart|website=[[Gaon Chart]]|language=ko}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:4em;font-size:90%\" |[[Billboard charts|US<br />World]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/world-digital-songs|title=World Digital Songs|work=[[Billboard charts|Billboar