{"title_page": "Roop Nagar", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}'''Roop Nagar''' is a residential district in [[Delhi]], India.  It is close to the [[Delhi metro]] station [[Vishwa Vidyalaya metro station|Vishwavidyalaya Metro Station]] and the  [[GTB Nagar metro station|GTB Nagar Metro Station]].  It is next to the Kamla Nagar market of [[North Delhi]] and the [[Delhi University]], North Campus.\n \nRoop Nagar includes a police station, [[Fire_station|fire station]], four government [[Secondary_school|secondary schools]], and seven parks. It contains the Manka-Meshwari temple, a Lordess [[Durga]] temple. Other temples include the Radha-Gobind temple and a [[Digambar Jain Mahasabha|Digambar Jain]] temple along with an [[Upashray|upasharay]].\n\n==References==\nDelhi Road Guide (Colliers International).\n\n{{coord missing|Delhi}}\n\n[[Category:Neighbourhoods in Delhi]]\n\n\n{{Delhi-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}'''Roop Nagar''' is a residential district in [[Delhi]], India.  It is close to the [[Delhi metro]] station [[Vishwa Vidyalaya metro station|Vishwavidyalaya Metro Station]] and the  [[GTB Nagar metro station|GTB Nagar Metro Station]].  It is next to the Kamla Nagar market of [[North Delhi]] and the [[Delhi University]], North Campus.\n \nRoop Nagar includes a police station, fire station, four government [[Secondary_school|secondary schools]], and seven parks. It contains the Manka-Meshwari temple, a Lordess [[Durga]] temple. Other temples include the Radha-Gobind temple and a [[Digambar Jain Mahasabha|Digambar Jain]] temple along with an [[Upashray|upasharay]].\n\n==References==\nDelhi Road Guide (Colliers International).\n\n{{coord missing|Delhi}}\n\n[[Category:Neighbourhoods in Delhi]]\n\n\n{{Delhi-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Gdrged", "label": "safe", "comment": "fire station interlinked", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roop_Nagar"}
